    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Clarifying the docs `--ip=*` is identical to `--ip=0.0.0.0`, which is to say \"listen on all interfaces\".  Now, this does not contain any information about the actual IP of the machine, though it is _accessible_ on every IP that points to it.  The `location` is the value used for resolving this ambiguity.  The default value for this is\n\n```\nsocket.gethostbyname_ex(socket.gethostname())[-1][-1]\n```\n\nWhich is typically the external IP of a machine, but not always.  If your machine cannot guess its own external IP, you have to specify this as `location`.  This ambiguity doesn't come up if you specify a particular IP.\n\nI'll try to add some explanation of this to the docs, and maybe even some fallback code that should get the right IP in your case.\n"
  },
